                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>He entered the 14th of December 1779, and he run away the 25th of November 1780; the R was taken off by the Commissioners of the Navy; whoever came was 
               <persName id="t17840421-17-person321">
                  Amos
                   Anderson
               <interp inst="t17840421-17-person321" type="surname" value="Anderson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17840421-17-person321" type="given" value="Amos"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17840421-17-person321" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             the party, it was not by letter of attorney; whenever it is paid in person it is marked party, whenever it is received by attorney, it is marked attorney.</p>
               <p>CAPT. 
               <persName id="t17840421-17-person322">
